    <div class="header">
        <h1>Watson: The Duel in the Sun and Beyond</h1>
        <h3>A Cinematic Exploration of Golf Legend Tom Watson's Life, Triumphs, and Legacy</h3>
        <p>Runtime: 90 minutes | Format: Feature-length documentary (4K)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Logline</h2>
        <p>This documentary chronicles the life of Tom Watson, an eight-time major champion whose career spans five decades, exploring his Midwestern roots, historic rivalry with Jack Nicklaus, legendary Open Championship victories, and his enduring impact on golf and philanthropy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Synopsis</h2>
        <p><em>Watson: The Duel in the Sun and Beyond</em> is a three-act journey through the life of one of golf's most revered figures:</p>
        
        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Act</th>
                <th>Focus</th>
                <th>Key Elements</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Act 1</td>
                <td>Origins</td>
                <td>Kansas City roots, early struggles, Byron Nelson mentorship</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Act 2</td>
                <td>Open Dominance</td>
                <td>1977 Duel in the Sun, 1982 Pebble Beach miracle, 2009 Turnberry</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Act 3</td>
                <td>Legacy</td>
                <td>ALS advocacy, Watson Links program, personal reflections</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>

